MONTVILLE, Maine (AP) — A house fire caused by an explosion killed three people in Maine when a man tried to light a stove during a gas leak, police said. The explosion happened on Wednesday in Montville. Police said it killed homeowner Stuart Nichols, 74; Rocco Taddeo, 88, of Montville; and Robert Gorham, 78, of Buxton.Police said one of Nichols’ appliances was experiencing a gas leak when Taddeo was attempting to light the stove. They said Nichols had recently acquired a used propane-powered cooking stove for his kitchen.Nichols and Gorham were outside the house at the time of the explosion. The force of the explosion threw Nichols and Gorham away from the residence and into some nearby trees, police said.Police said Taddeo died from injuries caused by the blast and fire. Nichols and Gorham died from injuries while being treated at Maine Medical Center in Portland.Nine fire departments from the area assisted the Montville Fire Department in responding to the scene.